ENTRY            F0699   20251222   20260305   20260305       F105
SUBENT        F0699001   20251222   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                 10         29
TITLE      Polarization measurement of fast neutrons from the
           9Be(alpha,n)12C and the 13C(alpha,n)16O reaction using
           a high-pressure 4He-polarimeter in a new design
AUTHOR     (W.Weiss,W.Grum,J.W.Hammer,M.Koch,G.Schreder)
INSTITUTE  (2GERTHS)
REFERENCE  (J,NIM/A,292,359,1990)
FACILITY   (DYNAM,2GERTHS) Stuttgart facility SCORPION.
INC-SOURCE Gas pressure: maximum 180 bar; test pressure: 250 bar;
           gas mixture: 95% helium-4, 5% xenon;
           volume: 120 ml ~ 1.8 g 4He at 170 bar;
           inner cell diameter: 46 mm.
DETECTOR   Four shielded neutron detectors (NE 213) were
           positioned and the range of the accessible reaction
           angles was between 21 and 124 degr. with a symmetric
           position of left and right detector. The minimum
           angular distance between two detectors was limited by
           the extension of the detector shielding to 42 degr.
           Two detectors were at a forward scattering angle
           of 50 degr and two detectors under a backscattering
           angle of 124 degr.
METHOD     (TOF,DSCAT,LRASY)
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
           The errors of the present experiment could be kept
           small because of the use of the SCORPION facility
           favoring small systematic errors and the fourfold
           redundant measurement.
HISTORY    (20030716C)
           (20251222A) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
           Subents 004 and 005 were merged.
ENDBIB              29
